categories.category: Communes of the Province of Salerno

parameters.name: Albanella
parameters.saint:
Sophia of Rome and
Matthew the Evangelist

bdy.p:
Albanella is a town and comune in the province of Salerno in the
Campania region of south-western
Italy
. It is located 51 kilometers from the city of Salerno.

The Church of Saint Sophia (La Chiesa di Santa Sofia) was built in the year 1500. The town slogan is "la terra degli ulivi," which translates to "the land of the olive trees" in English. Olive oil is one of the principal products of the town.
